action_packages.description: Search for messages, create drafts and send emails.

actions.description:
Search Google emails with a query filter.
Please inform user if there are more than `max_results` emails.
actions.name: search_emails

actions.description:
Update existing draft email by its draft id.
If draft_id is unknown then use action "get_email_content" to get the draft_id.

The recipients can be given with `to`, `cc` and `bcc` parameters as a comma separated list.
actions.name: update_draft

actions.description: Send draft email by its draft id.
actions.name: send_draft

actions.description:
Create a draft of an email.
The recipients can be given with `to`, `cc` and `bcc` parameters as a comma separated list.
actions.name: create_draft

actions.description:
Get Google email content with specific email id or with
a query filter.
actions.name: get_email_content

actions.description: Removes label(s) from emails using Google Email labels with a specific email id or with a query filter.
actions.name: remove_labels

actions.description:
Send the email to the recipient(s) using the Gmail API.
The recipients can be given with `to`, `cc` and `bcc` parameters as a comma separated list.
actions.name: send_email

actions.description:
Moves emails using Google Email labels with a specific email id or with a query filter.
Maximum of 100 emails can be moved at a time (set that on "all").

Email can be moved to a label or to the trash (label="TRASH").
actions.name: move_email

actions.description: Get list of drafts or filter drafts with a query.
actions.name: list_drafts

action_packages.name: Google Calendar
action_packages.description: List calendars and search, create and update events in your Google Calendar.

actions.description: Update an existing Google Calendar event with dynamic arguments.
actions.name: update_event

actions.description: Creates a new event in the specified calendar.
actions.name: create_event

actions.description:
List all events in the user's primary calendar between the given dates.
To aggregate all events across calendars, call this method for each calendar returned by list_calendars endpoint.
Ideally a start and end date should always be provided, otherwise we will look in the whole future or past.
actions.name: list_events

actions.description: List all calendars that the user is subscribed to.
actions.name: list_calendars

action_packages.name: Google Docs
action_packages.description: Get contents of Google Docs as Markdown

actions.description:
Get a Google Document by its name.
If multiple documents with the same name are found,
you need to use the ID of the document to load it.
Hint: Copy-pasting the URL of the document in the Agent will allow it to fetch the document by ID

Apostrophes in the title need to be escaped with a backslash.
The result is the Document formatted using the Extended Markdown Syntax.
actions.name: get_document_by_name

actions.description: Get a Google Document by its ID. The result is the Document formatted using the Extended Markdown Syntax.
actions.name: get_document_by_id

actions.description:
Create a new Google Document from an Extended Markdown string.
Args:
    title: The Google Document title
    body: The Google Document body as an Extended Markdown string.
    oauth_access_token: The OAuth2 Google access token
actions.name: create_document

actions.description:
Appends text formated using Extended Markdown syntax to an existing Google Document by its ID.
Args:
    document_id: The Google Document ID
    body: The Google Document body as an Extended Markdown string
    oauth_access_token: The OAuth2 Google access token
actions.name: append_to_document_by_id

actions.description:
Appends text formated using Extended Markdown syntax to an existing Google Document by its name.
Args:
    name: The Google Document name
    body: The Google Document body as an Extended Markdown string
    oauth_access_token: The OAuth2 Google access token
actions.name: append_to_document_by_name
